    "As shown in Figure 7, the photosensitizers undergo excitation upon absorbing a photon, transitioning from the singlet ground state to a higher-energy state.",
    "In this regard, the energy is transferred from one molecular entity to another without an actual transfer of electrons.",
    "Hence, in photosensitizers, energy transfer occurs through the process of intersystem crossing (Yu et al., 2022).",
    "There are two main types of energy transfer, which are Radiative Energy Transfer (Forster Resonance Energy Transfer, (FRET)) and Non-Radiative Energy Transfer (Dexter Energy Transfer (DET)) (Calçada et al., 2019; Enhanced Photodynamic et al., 2022; van der Meer, 2013; Tavakkoli Yaraki et al., 2022).",
    "The FRET is an Radiative Energy Transfer process that occurs between two molecules (usually chromophores) nearby."
